BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313424738@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T000655Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260310T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260310T200000
SUMMARY:Mindfulness Tuesday Meditation: Cultivating Consciousness
DESCRIPTION:Meditate with a Monk in Sonoma County\nJoin us for a transformative workshop on mindfulness meditation and cultivating consciousness. Dive deep into the teachings of Theravada Buddhism\, focusing on insight meditation to develop a clear understanding of the nature of the mind and consciousness. This workshop will include guided meditation sessions to help you strengthen your meditation practice and cultivate mindfulness in your daily life. Whether you are a beginner or an experienced meditator\, this workshop offers a welcoming space to explore the depths of your own consciousness and enhance your spiritual journey. Come together with like-minded individuals to deepen your practice and connect with the wisdom of Theravada Buddhism.\nOur sessions are led by Bhikkhunis closely associated with our Dhammadharini Sangha. Check out Dhammadharini Sangha at [https://www.dhammadharini.net/](https://www.dhammadharini.net/)\nRegister for this event on Dhammadharini's website:\n[https://www.dhammadharini.net/event-details/tuesday-evening-meditation-dhamma-talk-2](https://www.dhammadharini.net/event-details/tuesday-evening-meditation-dhamma-talk-2)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/meditate-with-a-monk-in-sonoma-county/events/313424738/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260219T033606Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T033606Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/3/5/5/600_530865909.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313493742@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T000655Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T100000
SUMMARY:Join us for Guided Buddhist Meditation and time for questions
DESCRIPTION:Meditate with a Monk in Sonoma County\nNew and experienced meditators are welcome. We will start with direct guidance to begin the practice and allow time to experience the silence of meditation on your own. There will be time at the end for your questions regarding meditation practice.\n\nYou may stay on for a potluck meal at 11:00 am. Welcome to bring a dish to share.\n\nThis is followed by Sutta Study program from 1:00 to 2:30 pm.\n\nWe meet outdoors in the Dhammadharini Monastery Garden in the Sala Pavillion\, as long as conducive weather lasts.\n\nCome in person\, or register at [here](https://www.dhammadharini.net/event-details/sunday-morning-guided-meditation-questions-2) to attend online
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/meditate-with-a-monk-in-sonoma-county/events/313493742/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260223T174611Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260223T174611Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/f/5/2/600_513320306.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313493854@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T000655Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T100000
SUMMARY:Mindfulness Sunday Meditation: Cultivating Consciousness
DESCRIPTION:Meditate with a Monk in Sonoma County\nJoin us for a transformative workshop on mindfulness meditation and cultivating consciousness. Dive deep into the teachings of Theravada Buddhism\, focusing on insight meditation to develop a clear understanding of the nature of the mind and consciousness. This workshop will include guided meditation sessions to help you strengthen your meditation practice and cultivate mindfulness in your daily life. Whether you are a beginner or an experienced meditator\, this workshop offers a welcoming space to explore the depths of your own consciousness and enhance your spiritual journey. Come together with like-minded individuals to deepen your practice and connect with the wisdom of Theravada Buddhism\, and provide an opportunity to deepen mindfulness\, wisdom\, and inner stillness.\nOur sessions are led by Bhikkhunis closely associated with our Dhammadharini Sangha. Check out the [recording from the past event](https://youtube.com/live/s07U2kzWoWk?feature=share) on our YouTube channel.\nYou’re also welcome to join us in person at Dhammadharini Monastery\, in the peaceful setting of our outdoor Dana Sala Pavilion\nRegister for this event on Dhammadharini's website to receive the address:\n[https://www.dhammadharini.net/event-details/sunday-morning-guided-meditation-questions-2](https://www.dhammadharini.net/event-details/sunday-morning-guided-meditation-questions-2)\nCheck out the sangha website at\n[https://www.dhammadharini.net](https://www.dhammadharini.net/)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/meditate-with-a-monk-in-sonoma-county/events/313493854/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260223T174817Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260223T174817Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/3/7/8/600_530865944.jpeg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:event_313497459@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T000655Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T143000
SUMMARY:Read and discuss the teachings of the Buddha
DESCRIPTION:Meditate with a Monk in Sonoma County\nWe study the early Buddhist texts by reading aloud and discussing. The reading will be announced each week\n\n1:00pm. Meditation\n1:15-2:30pm. Sutta reading and discussion\n\nYou may come early for a potluck meal at 11:00 am. Welcome to bring a dish to share.\n\nWe meet outdoors in the Dhammadharini Monastery's Garden in the Sala Pavillion\, as long as conducive weather lasts.\n\nCome in person\, or register at [here](https://www.dhammadharini.net/event-details/sunday-morning-guided-meditation-questions-2) to attend online
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/meditate-with-a-monk-in-sonoma-county/events/313497459/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260223T212748Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260223T212748Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/3/d/9/600_480545081.jpeg
END:VEVENT
